== Style.js ==

An easy to use JavaScript library providing CSS preprocessing and a myriad of color manipulation functions.

=== CSS Preprocessing ===

Style.js allows developers to utilize the full power of JavaScript to generate CSS.

Example:

<code>var color = '#06c';<br>
<br>
new Style({<br>
	p: {<br>
		background_color: color.toHSLA(),<br>
		color: selectForeground(color).toHSLA()<br>
	}.extend(<br>
		CSS.borderRadius(Math.floor(Math.random() * 11) + 0)<br>
		)<br>
});</code>

